<p>this is my web service</p>  <pre><code>@POST     @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_PLAIN)     @Path("/sumPost")     public String sumPost(@QueryParam("x") int x, @QueryParam("y") int y) {         return (x + y) + "";     } </code></pre>  <p>and i am calling it like this:</p>  <pre><code>HttpPost httpPost = new HttpPost(                 "bla bla bla");         ArrayList&lt;NameValuePair&gt; parameters = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();         parameters.add(new BasicNameValuePair("x", "3"));         parameters.add(new BasicNameValuePair("y", "4"));         httpPost.setEntity(new UrlEncodedFormEntity(parameters));         HttpResponse response = client.execute(httpPost);         String responseString = new BasicResponseHandler()                 .handleResponse(response);         System.out.println(responseString); </code></pre>  <p>i kept getting zero as a response. However, when i change the method to get and i pass the parameters in the url, i get it correctly working. so what do i miss here? </p>  <p>i added the parameters as this question did <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/8120220/how-to-use-parameters-with-httppost">How to use parameters with HttpPost</a></p>